# Project Memory Rules

## Core rules

- Always read `/docs/PROJECT_VISION.md` before making product-level decisions.
- Always read `/docs/GAME_RULES.md` before changing game logic.
- Always read `/docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` first for «what works / what next» on the frontend.
- Always read `/docs/PROJECT_ROADMAP.md` before starting implementation.
- Always read `/docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` for block rhythm (UI → tech → backend brief).
- Always read `/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` before changing `src/` structure, layers, imports, or feature boundaries.
- Always check `/docs/API_CONTRACT.md` and `/docs/INTEGRATION.md` before creating or changing API/service contracts.
- Backend specs and full integration guide live in **`fantasy-predictions-back`** only — no duplicate `BACKEND_*` docs on the frontend.
- Cursor layer rules: `00-core.mdc` (always), `10-architecture.mdc` (structure/refactor tasks).
- Always update `/docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` when wiring or removing a live API endpoint.
- Always update `/docs/SPRINT_LOG.md` after meaningful implementation progress.
- Always update `/docs/DECISION_LOG.md` when a product, technical or architecture decision is made.
- Always add postponed ideas to `/docs/BACKLOG.md`.
- Always update `/docs/GLOSSARY.md` when introducing a new project term.
- Always update `/docs/UX_NOTES.md` when changing UX principles, onboarding, mobile-first behavior or interface flow.

## Product safety rules

- Never turn the project into a betting, casino, gambling or real-money wagering app.
- Never add real-money bets, withdrawals, deposits, bookmaker branding or casino-like UX.
- Virtual currency is only an in-game resource.
- Monetization must not create pay-to-win mechanics.
- Paid features may include cosmetics, no ads, profile styling, badges, themes or advanced stats.
- The product must feel like football RPG + fantasy football manager + prediction league, not a sportsbook.

## Git commits

- **Mandatory format:** `FP-<N>: <short summary>` — see `.cursor/rules/git-commit-format.mdc`.
- Ask for task id if unknown before committing.

## Documentation workflow

After every meaningful code change, update documentation if needed:

- changed game rules → update `GAME_RULES.md`
- changed roadmap/progress → update `PROJECT_ROADMAP.md` or `SPRINT_LOG.md`
- closed or started a delivery block → update `SPRINT_LOG.md` Block section + `DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` if rhythm changes
- added new endpoint/service contract → update `API_CONTRACT.md`
- made product/architecture decision → update `DECISION_LOG.md`
- changed frontend structure or architecture policy → update `ARCHITECTURE.md` (and exception registry if applicable)
- added future idea → update `BACKLOG.md`
- added new term → update `GLOSSARY.md`
- changed UX behavior → update `UX_NOTES.md`

Do not silently change product direction.

## Tech dependency rule

When installing libraries, always prefer latest stable versions.

Before adding a library:

- check current `package.json`;
- avoid unnecessary dependencies;
- prefer simple and maintainable solutions;
- do not install outdated packages unless there is a strong reason;
- document important dependency decisions in `DECISION_LOG.md`.

## Current project template rule

The app is a **bare React 19 + Vite 8 + TypeScript** template.

Before implementing features, check:

- `package.json` — scripts and dependencies;
- `docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` — what is wired to API today;
- `vite.config.ts` — `@/` alias, port 3000;
- Phase 1: router, ESLint, Prettier, `shared/api/httpClient.ts`, live backend.

See `PROJECT_ROADMAP.md` and `SPRINT_LOG.md` for roadmap vs done.

## Product summary (quick reference)

Mobile-first football prediction RPG / fantasy football manager:

- **Exact Score** is the main Player input;
- system derives **Prediction Components**;
- **Energy** (100 per match) is distributed by **Defensive / Balanced / Aggressive / Manual Style**;
- **Official Prediction** affects **Official Rating**; others go to **Shadow Stats**;
- **Club**, **Bot Club**, **Bot Player**, **Virtual Match**, **Division**, **Team Energy** for league play;
- no real-money wagering; monetization later: ads / subscription / cosmetics only.
